title: ICE in MIR inlining with -Zmir-opt-level=3

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I found this ICE originally in `encoding_rs`, and minimized here. I think this panic is deliberate, but wasn't reachable (or wasn't easy to reach) until recently when another problem with `-Zmir-opt-level=3` was fixed. ```Rust pub fn outer() -> usize { inner() } fn index() -> usize { loop {} } #[inline] fn inner() -> usize { let buffer = &[true]; let index = index(); if buffer[index] { index } else { 0 } } ``` `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.0-nightly (46160e6fa 2022-12-24) binary: rustc commit-hash: 46160e6fa91eba00d7c3b554646149adc82717f2 commit-date: 2022-12-24 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left != right)` left: `Index(_0)`, right: `Index(_0)`', compiler/rustc_mir_transform/src/inline.rs:1035:13 ```
